## Smart Tool Selection Summary

When you catch yourself about to:

| Instead of | Use |
|-----------|-----|
| Grep for "who calls this" | `trace_path(direction="inbound")` |
| Grep for "what does this call" | `trace_path(direction="outbound")` |
| Manual file search for functions | `search_graph` |
| Walking the call stack manually | `trace_path(direction="both")` |
| Looking for unused code manually | `search_graph(max_degree=0)` |
| Checking git diff impact manually | `detect_changes` |
| Manually opening browser to inspect | `browser_navigate` + `browser_snapshot` |
| Taking manual screenshots | `browser_take_screenshot` |
| Manually clicking through a web UI | Playwright interaction tools |
| Forgetting what was decided before | `memory_recall` |
| Not saving important decisions | `memory_save` |

Always prefer MCP tools over manual file traversal or grep when the corresponding MCP tool exists.
